The bug is because of the following code in your site&#39;s `meta`:
```
&lt;meta name=&quot;keywords&quot; content=&quot;{{site.tags}}&quot;&gt;
```

`site.tags` is a *hash* of all posts tagged to a given string.
A *hash* here denotes a container of key-value pairs. For example:
```
{&quot;foo&quot; =&gt; &quot;bar&quot;, &quot;alpha&quot; =&gt; &quot;beta&quot;}
```

---

---

## Solutions

Use some other variable to denote the keywords. For example, `keywords`.
In your config file, replace the key `tags` with `keywords`.

```
keywords: [
  &quot;HTML&quot;,
  &quot;Python&quot;,
  &quot;CSS&quot;,
  &quot;Coding&quot;,
  &quot;Blog&quot;
]
```
Then update your `head.html` include:
```
&lt;meta name=&quot;keywords&quot; content=&quot;{{ site.keywords }}&quot;&gt;
```

---

Regarding the rendering of checkboxes, you need to know that kramdown considers all lines with 4 leading spaces to denote a code-block.
Therefore the following
```
{% for post in site.posts %}
    {% for tag in post.tags %}
        &lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot;&gt;{{tag}}&lt;br&gt;
    {% endfor %}
{% endfor %}
```
will only produce
```
    &lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot;&gt;code&lt;br&gt;

    &lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot;&gt;test&lt;br&gt;

    &lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot;&gt;example&lt;br&gt;

    &lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot;&gt;python&lt;br&gt;
```
(They&#39;re not rendered as HTML inputs but as raw code.)

---
To see the internal representation of any object you intend to use in Liquid, you can pass it to the `inspect` filter. For example, to see what `site.tags` (or `site.categories` even) are actually, you could inspect them via:
```
&lt;pre&gt;{{ site.tags | inspect }}&lt;/pre&gt;
```

