Given that `players` is defined as a global variable, you need to reset in your constructor, something like this:

    class Game:
    
        def __init__(self, n):
            players = dict()

Having a global variable is a bad practice in any language, see [this](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/19158339/why-are-global-variables-evil). If players is a property of the `Game` objects you should do instead:

    class Game:
    
        def __init__(self, n):
            self.players = { }  # dictionary construction expression

